Any time your mobile phone is switched on and has signal, your network provider knows where you are and has identifying information about your phone and SIM card. If you are concerned about your location being know to an adversary, or about other forms of surveillance, you need to be aware of the ways in which your identity is linked to your mobile use.}
\par \pard\plain \s24\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ltrpar\cf2\dbch\af9\langfe2052\dbch\af11\afs24\alang1081\kerning1\loch\f3\fs24\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \scaps0\caps0\cf1\strike0\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\dbch\af10\fs22 \u9679\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls3 \li1440\ri0\lin1440\rin0\fi360\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi360{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Any communication between your phone and the mobile network includes at least two numbers that uniquely identify your phone and SIM card. The IMEI is a number that uniquely identifies the phone . The IMSI is a number that uniquely identifies the SIM card. This information is part of the network\u8217\'92s records, and is noted and saved (\u8216\'91logged\u8217\'92) whenever you make or receive a call or text message, or use mobile data services.}
\par \pard\plain \s24\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ltrpar\cf2\dbch\af9\langfe2052\dbch\af11\afs24\alang1081\kerning1\loch\f3\fs24\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \scaps0\caps0\cf1\strike0\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\dbch\af10\fs22 \u9679\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls3 \li1440\ri0\lin1440\rin0\fi360\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi360{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
To be able to route calls, texts and data to the tower to which your phone is currently connected, the mobile network also needs to know your location. This information may be logged continuously, and is also recorded and saved when you make or receive a call or text message, or use mobile data services. This phone could be positively identified with you if it consistently appears in the area of your home or other locations that could be associated with you. For more information about location tracking, see our }{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://dev.safermobile.org/resource/geolocation-primer/" }\cs16\cf3\ul\ulc0\langfe1033\alang1033\lang1033\cf5\ul\ulc0{\fldrslt \cf3\ul\ulc0\langfe1033\alang1033\lang1033\rtlch \ltrch\loch
primer on geolocation}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
}}.}
